collectionCode: Helfer H. 1936. The fishery grounds near Alexandria. VIII Pantopoda. Notes et memoires No 16
habitat: dark sandy bottom, Caluerpa, little brown algae, Cymodocea
identificationReferences: Helfer H. 1936. The fishery grounds near Alexandria. VIII Pantopoda. Notes et memoires No 16
institutionCode: Hellenic Centre for Marine Research-Institute of Marine Biology, Biotechnology and Aquaculture
locationRemarks: Coordinates, coordinates uncertainty and locality estimated by MedOBIS data management team by gis and google earth, based on the map in publication and in (Adolf Steuer.Preliminary report.The Fishery Grounds Near Alexandria. Notes and Memories No 8.)
samplingProtocol: There was no specific information about sampling method.By the Preliminary Report seems to be the same as the whole expedition-dredge with an opening of 20x70 cm (1400 cm2).Depth is measured in fathom=1.8288 metres.All the excursions were one day trip. For work near the coast a small rowing boat was available. References: Steuer A. 1935. The fishery grounds near Alexandria. 1. Preliminary Report, Notes and Memoirs No 8. Fisheries Research Directorate, Egypt.
taxonRemarks: name as in original file:Tanystylum conirostre
